notesData.title: Meal plan
notesData.content:
7-Day Anti-Inflammatory Meal Plan

 Monday
  Breakfast: Greek yogurt with raspberries, chia + flax seeds
  Lunch: Spinach & cucumber salad with tomatoes, red onion, celery, olive oil + lemon dressing, tuna
 on top.
  Dinner: Roasted Brussels sprouts, sweet potatoes, carrots with olive oil, paprika, cumin, garlic (with chicken)

 Tuesday
  Breakfast: Overnight oats with Greek yogurt, oats, chia, raspberries, olive oil drizzle.
  Lunch: Broccoli, bell pepper, and scallion stir-fry with garlic, olive oil, black pepper. Side of brown
 rice or quinoa.
  Dinner: Baked sweet potato with Greek yogurt, garlic, parsley. Side cucumber salad with apple
 cider vinegar.

 Wednesday
  Breakfast: Greek yogurt + flax + strawberries
  Lunch: Tuna salad with celery, red onion, parsley, olive oil, lemon, black pepper. 
  Dinner: Some red meat or pork chop with Roasted asparagus + carrots with garlic + paprika, olive oil drizzle, side of lentil soup.

 Thursday
  Breakfast: Yogurt with chia + raspberries + touch of honey (optional).
  Lunch: Spinach salad with cucumber, cherry tomatoes, lemon dressing, olive oil. Add tuna or
 veggies.
  Dinner: Garlic sauted Brussels sprouts + bell peppers, sweet potato mash with olive oil and cumin. (with chicken)

 Friday
  Breakfast: Overnight oats with Greek yogurt, chia, flax, blueberries
  Lunch: Cucumber + red onion + tomato salad with oregano, lemon, apple cider vinegar. Side lentil
 soup or roasted carrots.
 Dinner: Oven-roasted asparagus + broccoli with olive oil + pepper, side sweet potato fries.

 Saturday
  Breakfast: 2 eggs with olive oil + scallions, side sauted spinach + tomato + garlic, optional yogurt
 with raspberries.
  Lunch: Spinach salad with tuna, celery, parsley, lemon, olive oil
  Dinner: Roasted carrots + sweet potatoes + Brussels sprouts with olive oil, cumin, black pepper,
 paprika

 Sunday
  Breakfast: Omelette with spinach, bell pepper, onion, garlic, olive oil, oregano.
  Lunch: Cucumber + celery salad with apple cider vinegar, lentil soup with garlic + cumin.
  Dinner: Asparagus, sweet potato, and roasted cherry tomato medley, olive oil, black pepper, lemon,
 yogurt with flax + raspberries.

Snack:
Pistachio / Pumpkin seed
Side of tangerine or grapes or pomegranate

Extra 2: Red wine vinegar + Oregano/Parsley + Scallions + Paprika

notesData.title: Focus
notesData.content:
Learn new skills (language, instrument, coding, puzzles)
Memory games (Lumosity, Elevate, or simple recall drills)


Your Core Energy & Health Routine

 Nutrition

Focus on:
		Protein: chicken, eggs, Greek yogurt, fish, beans  aim for 1.21.5 g per kg of body weight daily.
		Healthy fats: olive oil, avocado, nuts, omega-3s (already covered by your supplement).
		Complex carbs: oats, quinoa, brown rice, sweet potato, or whole-grain toast.

 Goal: build balanced meals that fuel energy steadily  no sugar spikes or long gaps without food.



 Movement
		Walk twice daily (10 min each):
		Morning walk  wake up your body and metabolism.
		Evening walk  improve digestion and circulation.
		Gentle bodyweight exercises and stretches daily:
		Wall push-ups, squats, planks, shoulder rolls, chest stretch, neck mobility.

 Goal: re-activate your muscles and blood flow after years of sitting.



 Posture & Work Setup
		Use a standing desk or change positions every 4560 minutes.
		Stretch shoulders, chest, and neck whenever you stand up.

 Goal: improve circulation, posture, and reduce back/neck stiffness.



 Sleep Routine
		Sleep time: 11 p.m. every night (consistent bedtime = stable energy).
		Wind-down routine:
		No screens 45 min before bed.
		Try slow nasal breathing or a 5-min relaxation track.
		Keep the room cool and dark.

 Goal: restore circadian rhythm, support hormone balance, and improve recovery.



 Simple Daily Checklist
		Eat balanced meals (protein + fat + complex carbs)
		Walk 10 min AM
		Walk 10 min PM
		Stretch / light exercise
		Stand up every hour
		Sleep at 11 p.m.
		510 min breathing before bed

notesData.title: Workout Plans
notesData.content:
Posture / Breathing


Mini Squats (10 reps)
Feet shoulder-width apart, bend knees slightly (like sitting on an invisible chair), then back up.
Strengthens quads and glutes without stress.
Calf Raises (15 reps)
Rise onto your toes, hold 2 seconds, slowly lower.
Improves circulation and ankle stability.
Standing Hamstring Stretch (20 sec per leg)
Straighten one leg on a low surface (like a chair), lean forward gently.
Quad Stretch (20 sec per leg)
Standing, grab one ankle and pull toward your glute  stretches front of thigh.
Hip Circles or Weight Shifts (30 sec)
Gently rotate hips or shift weight leftright to keep joints fluid.
